The paper discusses principles of learning and discovery in intelligent agents, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on unsupervised learning and reinforcement learning suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The discussion of subjective beauty and creativity suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also relevant. The use of compressibility as a measure of interestingness suggests that cs.SD (Sound) may be relevant, as this is a common measure in audio compression. Finally, the discussion of world models and descriptions suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) may also be relevant.
